# ============================================================
# WHITELIST GITIGNORE — SENSITIVE DATA PROTECTION
# ============================================================
# This repo will contain/reference an Obsidian vault with highly
# sensitive personal data (journal entries, chat history, recovery
# content). Safety-first: everything is ignored by default.
# Only explicitly approved paths are tracked.
# ============================================================

# Ignore everything at the top level by default
/*

# --- Explicitly tracked root files ---
!.gitignore
!CLAUDE.md

# --- Explicitly tracked directories ---
!.claude/
!.github/
!creek-vault/
!scripts/

# ============================================================
# OBSIDIAN VAULT — SENSITIVE CONTENT (NEVER TRACK)
# ============================================================
# If the Creek-Vault Obsidian structure is created in or linked
# from this repo, these patterns ensure sensitive content stays
# out of version control regardless of where it appears.
# Only 00-Creek-Meta/Scripts/ should ever be tracked.
# ============================================================

# Vault content directories (personal data, fragments, journals)
**/01-Fragments/
**/02-Threads/
**/03-Eddies/
**/04-Praxis/
**/05-Wavelength/
**/06-Frequencies/
**/07-Voice/
**/08-Decisions/
**/09-Reference/
**/10-Liminal/

# Vault meta directories (except Scripts/)
**/00-Creek-Meta/Templates/
**/00-Creek-Meta/Ontology/
**/00-Creek-Meta/Processing-Log/

# ============================================================
# DEVELOPMENT ARTIFACTS
# ============================================================

# Python
**/__pycache__/
**/.venv/
**/venv/
**/virtualenv/
**/*.py[cod]
**/*.egg-info/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/*.egg
**/.eggs/
**/htmlcov/
**/.coverage
**/.coverage.*
**/coverage.xml
**/reports/

